I want to be able to use regular expressions to not just perform string replacements, but also string transposition.

In another example, I could have
if (TYPE_A == value) {
  // do something
} else if (TYPE_B == value) {
  // do something else
}

and I want to turn it into
if (TYPESTR_A.equals(value)) {
  // do something
} else if (TYPESTR_B.equals(value)) {
  // do something else
}

I could write a regular expression find/replace where
find:TYPE_(.) == ([^ )]*)
replace:TYPESTR_\1.equals(\2)

basically, the backslash followed by a number represents whatever string was found using parenthesis, so now I can modify/transpose/replace whatever I want using regular expressions.

